section.def:
earth
                (地) means the conductive mass of the earth whose
            electric potential at any point is conventionally taken as zero;

earthing
                (接地) means connecting a conductor with
            earth;

switching
                (開關) means making or breaking a current under
            normal circuit conditions;

paragraph.content:
a place of public entertainment as defined in the Places of Public
                    Entertainment Ordinance (Cap. 172) other than a
                    sea-going vessel;
